<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1409,1868]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1482,1508]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bernardo, U. &amp; Gebiola, M. &amp; Xiao, Z. &amp; Zhu, C. - D. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Viggiani, G." box="[321,567,1482,1508]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="437 - 446" refId="ref42594" refString="Bernardo, U., Gebiola, M., Xiao, Z., Zhu, C. - D., Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Viggiani, G. (2013) Description of Synergus castaneus n. sp. (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) associated with an unknown gall on Castanea spp. (Fagaceae) in China. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 106 (4), 437 - 446. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / AN 13009" type="journal article" year="2013">
Bernardo 
<emphasis box="[431,480,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
suspected that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pujade-Villar, Bernardo &amp; Viggiani" authorityYear="2013" box="[736,873,1482,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Synergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis box="[736,873,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">S. castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be a gall maker; however, it was later reared from galls of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pujade-Villar et al. 2018 b)" baseAuthorityName="Pujade-Villar" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[303,801,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henryi">
<emphasis box="[303,483,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Andricus henryi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M." box="[497,793,1518,1544]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="131 - 139" refId="ref50418" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Guo, R., Wang, Y. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M. (2018 b) First record of an Andricus chestnut gall wasp from the Oriental Region: a new species from China (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Entomotaxonomia, 40 (2), 131 - 139." type="journal article" year="2018">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[655,704,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. 2018b
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1409,1868]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,356,1553,1580]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Remarks (2).</emphasis>
According to the original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pujade-Villar et al. 2014 c)" baseAuthorityName="Pujade-Villar" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[823,1294,1554,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Saphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulatus">
<emphasis box="[823,837,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[853,972,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">reticulatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R." box="[987,1286,1554,1580]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="43 - 48" refId="ref51398" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. (2014 c) Description of a new species of Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer from China (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini). Entomologica Fennica, 25, 43 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.33338 / ef. 41468" type="journal article" year="2014">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[1147,1198,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. 2014c
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, this species was reared from galls on branches and twigs of 
<taxonomicName box="[675,968,1590,1616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="aliena" variety="acutiserrata">
<emphasis box="[675,778,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Q. aliena</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[831,968,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">acutiserrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, this host plant was erroneously identified: it was actually a 
<taxonomicName box="[461,606,1626,1652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[461,567,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Castanea</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." box="[620,901,1626,1652]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="341 - 362" refId="ref46693" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Wang, Y., Melika, G., Guo, R., Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2021 a) A review of the species in the genus Synergus Hartig (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) from mainland China, with an updated key to Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental species. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 24 (1), 341 - 362. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. aspen. 2020.11.014" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis box="[765,814,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. 2021a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1409,1868]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,1661,1688]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Remarks (3).</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." box="[359,648,1662,1688]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="341 - 362" refId="ref46693" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Wang, Y., Melika, G., Guo, R., Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2021 a) A review of the species in the genus Synergus Hartig (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) from mainland China, with an updated key to Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental species. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 24 (1), 341 - 362. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. aspen. 2020.11.014" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis box="[500,549,1662,1688]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. (2021a)
</bibRefCitation>
said that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pujade-Villar, Bernardo &amp; Viggiani" authorityYear="2013" box="[753,890,1662,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Synergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis box="[753,890,1662,1688]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">S. castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was obtained from asexual galls of 
<taxonomicName box="[1286,1388,1662,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henryi">
<emphasis box="[1286,1388,1662,1688]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">A. henryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it was a typographical error: according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M." box="[624,936,1698,1724]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="131 - 139" refId="ref50418" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Guo, R., Wang, Y. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M. (2018 b) First record of an Andricus chestnut gall wasp from the Oriental Region: a new species from China (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Entomotaxonomia, 40 (2), 131 - 139." type="journal article" year="2018">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[781,830,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. (2018b)
</bibRefCitation>
, based on the adult morphology and the gall phenology females of 
<taxonomicName box="[401,504,1734,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henryi">
<emphasis box="[401,504,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">A. henryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably correspond to the sexual generation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
